#This is the installation guide for clusterjob (CJ).
#Copyright 2015 Hatef Monajemi (monajemi@stanford.edu)


(-) Clone clusterjob to a directory where you would like to install CJ
	git clone git@github.com:monajemi/clusterjob.git ~/CJ_install 
	
(-) Set path variables:

To add the path to install directory to @INC, please
add the following to your ~/.bashrc pr ~./profile
	
	export PERL5LIB=~/CJ_install/src
or
	export PERLLIB=~/CJ_install/src

To read more about setting path variable in perl, please 
visit: 
http://perlmaven.com/how-to-change-inc-to-find-perl-modules-in-non-standard-locations

(-) Add alias to your ~/.profile or ~/.bashrc:

	alias cj='perl ~/CJ_install/src/CJ.pl';



